2
00:00:03,410 --> 00:00:06,390
Hijikata and Okita have been captured by the mysterious man, Jigzaw,

3
00:00:06,390 --> 00:00:10,540
and locked up in a deserted building.

4
00:00:11,430 --> 00:00:17,630
In order to escape, they must obtain a single key provided by Jigzaw.

5
00:00:18,470 --> 00:00:24,430
But only one person can use the key to unlock his chains and escape the room.

6
00:00:24,950 --> 00:00:29,280
When one's shackle is released, the other's will explode.

7
00:00:30,470 --> 00:00:34,200
And if one of them doesn't escape soon,

8
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:39,460
the Shinsengumi station will be blown to pieces by Jigzaw's bomb.

9
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:43,640
Kill one comrade to save the others.

10
00:00:44,110 --> 00:00:53,130
That would be the game of death Jigzaw has given the Shinsengumi to test their strong bond.

11
00:00:54,040 --> 00:01:00,020
And as for the new assassin Jigzaw has unleashed...?

12
00:01:01,190 --> 00:01:04,850
What will happen to the Shinsengumi?

13
00:01:04,850 --> 00:01:07,270
Why are you doing the summary?!

14
00:01:07,270 --> 00:01:10,070
What will happen, my ass!

15
00:01:10,070 --> 00:01:11,760
You're the one who set this whole thing up!

16
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:13,730
Why are you talking like you have nothing to do with this?!

17
00:01:13,730 --> 00:01:16,500
The hell is wrong with your head?!

18
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:19,430
I'm being considerate for the audience who missed the previous episode.

19
00:01:19,430 --> 00:01:21,040
We want to help them understand what's going on.

20
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:23,440
How come you're nice to the audience?!

21
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:00,580
Th-That's...

22
00:03:00,580 --> 00:03:02,160
Wh-What...

23
00:03:02,160 --> 00:03:03,790
I would like to introduce...

24
00:03:04,540 --> 00:03:08,930
[Note: Kickzaw is a play on Kikuzo, the name of popular comic storyteller, Kikuzo Hayashiya]

25
00:03:04,540 --> 00:03:07,600
...my beloved dog, Kickzaw.

26
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,930
Isn't he adorable?

27
00:03:09,610 --> 00:03:11,650
He has an odd habit.

28
00:03:11,650 --> 00:03:15,850
He always tends to pick up shiny objects when we go for a walk.

29
00:03:15,850 --> 00:03:20,560
Well, let's see what he picked up today.

30
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:30,920
N-N-N-N-Not good!

31
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:31,870
This is bad!

32
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:32,980
Very bad!

33
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:35,090
He's definitely going to take it!

34
00:03:35,510 --> 00:03:36,930
This isn't the time to whine about details!

35
00:03:36,930 --> 00:03:38,540
Getting backstabbed is no longer the problem!

36
00:03:38,540 --> 00:03:40,380
If he takes it, it's over!

37
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:43,150
No more escape or preventing the station from blowing up!

38
00:03:44,230 --> 00:03:47,060
Huh? Hijikata-san, you're sweating really hard.

39
00:03:47,990 --> 00:03:51,270
Are you scared about the key being taken?

40
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:52,610
Huh? What?

41
00:03:52,610 --> 00:03:54,760
No way. Not at all.

42
00:03:54,760 --> 00:03:55,850
What are you talking about?

43
00:03:55,850 --> 00:03:57,430
I said we didn't need it.

44
00:03:57,430 --> 00:03:59,180
It's totally unnecessary.

45
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:01,390
That's right.

46
00:04:01,390 --> 00:04:04,120
We don't need that traitor's tool.

47
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,260
Don't need it.

48
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:07,990
We'll break out of here with our own power.

49
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:10,160
Hijikata!

50
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:12,060
Move one step.

51
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:14,990
I'll instantly purge you as a traitor!

52
00:04:14,990 --> 00:04:16,280
Sogo!

53
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:18,850
Do you understand the situation we're in?!

54
00:04:18,850 --> 00:04:20,370
Hurry up!

55
00:04:20,370 --> 00:04:22,710
Hurry up and betray me, Hijikata!

56
00:04:22,710 --> 00:04:24,260
Please, I'll give you 300 yen.

57
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:26,170
Go, Sogo!

58
00:04:26,170 --> 00:04:28,140
Don't be so stubborn!

59
00:04:28,140 --> 00:04:29,500
Please betray me already!

60
00:04:32,090 --> 00:04:33,360
K-Kickzaw!

61
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:33,970
Wait!

62
00:04:33,970 --> 00:04:34,960
Sit! Stay!

63
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:36,150
Shake hands! Stay!

64
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,240
Stay! Stay!

65
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,870
Can't you hear what I'm saying?!

66
00:04:38,870 --> 00:04:40,330
Want me to kill you, stupid dog?!

67
00:04:42,530 --> 00:04:43,420
